1
00:00:17,100 --> 00:00:19,320
Do you want to shower first?
The bathroom's over there.

2
00:00:21,830 --> 00:00:22,950
Did you bring a towel with you?

3
00:00:38,780 --> 00:00:39,230
Thank you.

4
00:00:41,160 --> 00:00:42,760
Did your parents ask about
you staying over?

5
00:00:44,770 --> 00:00:48,210
They didn't ask.
I said I'm staying at my partner's.

6
00:00:48,490 --> 00:00:51,370
Mom said hurry up
and make it official already.

7
00:00:51,860 --> 00:00:52,580
That's not true.

8
00:00:54,450 --> 00:00:58,070
Just kidding.
I said I'm staying at your place.

9
00:00:58,400 --> 00:01:01,890
They trust you.
They like you after meeting you.

10
00:01:04,000 --> 00:01:08,440
"From only playing basketball
and ignoring school,

11
00:01:08,850 --> 00:01:10,930
Akin helped him with his studies."

12
00:01:12,360 --> 00:01:14,330
That's what having
a good partner means.

13
00:01:16,600 --> 00:01:18,440
My dad didn't say that. I did.

14
00:01:19,500 --> 00:01:21,650
My parents trust you a lot.

15
00:01:22,039 --> 00:01:23,260
I'm trustworthy.

16
00:01:23,890 --> 00:01:25,539
But can you be trusted?

17
00:01:27,210 --> 00:01:30,660
Hmm, I'm not so sure about that.

18
00:01:32,289 --> 00:01:33,170
Go take a shower.

19
00:01:40,330 --> 00:01:42,710
Don't undress here.
Do it in the bathroom.

20
00:01:43,250 --> 00:01:43,979
Come on.

21
00:01:51,759 --> 00:01:53,050
I'll undress right here.

22
00:01:59,340 --> 00:02:00,630
We're close, aren't we?

23
00:02:10,789 --> 00:02:11,960
Why didn't you close
the door properly?

24
00:02:13,600 --> 00:02:16,410
If you want it closed, come do it.
I want to show off.

25
00:02:18,380 --> 00:02:22,840
Basketball muscles are solid.
Want to check?

26
00:02:23,500 --> 00:02:24,010
No.

27
00:02:29,070 --> 00:02:30,470
- 'Kin.
- Hm?

28
00:02:31,560 --> 00:02:32,500
Can you grab me a towel?

29
00:02:34,140 --> 00:02:35,230
Why didn't you bring one in?

30
00:02:35,860 --> 00:02:36,990
Come on, please get it for me.

31
00:02:44,200 --> 00:02:44,610
Here.

32
00:02:45,470 --> 00:02:46,700
Hey, Than.

33
00:02:48,490 --> 00:02:49,210
Thank you.

34
00:03:02,430 --> 00:03:05,650
People can be so cold-hearted.

35
00:03:06,260 --> 00:03:10,320
Letting a poor kid like me
sleep on the floor.

36
00:03:11,570 --> 00:03:13,980
Or you take the bed
and I sleep on the floor?

37
00:03:14,750 --> 00:03:17,220
Why don't we just sleep together?

38
00:03:17,890 --> 00:03:20,070
I'm your partner, you know.

39
00:03:20,290 --> 00:03:22,210
Partner my ass.
Don't talk nonsense.

40
00:03:23,820 --> 00:03:27,860
Ow, the floor is really hard.

41
00:03:28,240 --> 00:03:32,940
Stop whining.
Staying over is already a big step.

42
00:03:32,960 --> 00:03:36,870
We've been together
almost three months.

43
00:03:36,900 --> 00:03:39,040
Together? Don't push it.

44
00:03:40,750 --> 00:03:43,190
See? You're so mean.

45
00:03:44,010 --> 00:03:48,300
No pity for a young student athlete.

46
00:03:49,940 --> 00:03:51,600
You won't let me sleep comfortably.

47
00:03:52,420 --> 00:03:53,570
Next time, just go home.

48
00:03:55,470 --> 00:03:57,280
It's okay. This is fine for now.

49
00:03:57,829 --> 00:04:01,490
At least it's our first night
sleeping close.

50
00:04:02,430 --> 00:04:04,490
Come on, sleep. You talk too much.

51
00:04:05,090 --> 00:04:07,630
- Good night.
- Good night.

52
00:04:11,260 --> 00:04:13,430
Turn this way.

53
00:04:15,450 --> 00:04:15,950
Why?

54
00:04:18,620 --> 00:04:19,320
Can I hold your hand?

55
00:04:24,320 --> 00:04:25,090
Satisfied now?

56
00:04:31,400 --> 00:04:32,320
You silly kid.

57
00:05:12,680 --> 00:05:13,130
Than.

58
00:05:15,500 --> 00:05:17,550
I gave you my first kiss.

59
00:05:18,770 --> 00:05:23,130
A promise this 10th grader
will love you sincerely.

60
00:05:25,370 --> 00:05:26,350
Can I trust that?

61
00:05:27,710 --> 00:05:29,480
Or should I do it again?

62
00:05:30,280 --> 00:05:32,060
Enough. I believe you.

63
00:05:35,510 --> 00:05:39,670
You took my first kiss.
Take responsibility.

64
00:05:41,580 --> 00:05:43,570
Was that really your first kiss?

65
00:05:45,500 --> 00:05:46,940
You've never kissed anyone?

66
00:05:49,530 --> 00:05:50,030
Really?

67
00:05:52,690 --> 00:05:54,860
Answer me first.

68
00:05:57,440 --> 00:06:01,570
I'll remember it. August 8th.

69
00:06:02,430 --> 00:06:04,520
Our first kiss together.

70
00:07:23,780 --> 00:07:24,960
If I still have a chance,

71
00:07:25,620 --> 00:07:28,650
I won't let love be a secret again.

72
00:07:29,550 --> 00:07:31,720
Nut said the gym may close soon.

73
00:07:31,790 --> 00:07:33,040
Who are you going to battle?

74
00:07:33,330 --> 00:07:35,330
If you're ready, let's go.

75
00:07:36,659 --> 00:07:37,600
One, two, three.

76
00:07:37,740 --> 00:07:39,260
No matter what we face,

77
00:07:39,950 --> 00:07:42,320
please don't let go of
my hand again.

78
00:07:42,630 --> 00:07:45,250
Mawin is my brother's son.

79
00:07:45,560 --> 00:07:46,670
That's enough, Akin.

80
00:07:47,100 --> 00:07:49,540
Stop using Mawin as a stand-in.

81
00:07:49,940 --> 00:07:51,090
- Let's go.
- Wait, Meya.

82
00:07:51,970 --> 00:07:52,780
Meya!

83
00:08:34,409 --> 00:08:35,750
Teasing me this early?

84
00:08:36,740 --> 00:08:37,780
I thought you wouldn't wake up.

85
00:08:38,760 --> 00:08:39,659
Why wouldn't I?

86
00:08:41,350 --> 00:08:42,780
Because last night...

87
00:08:43,870 --> 00:08:47,340
Don't underestimate me.
I'm still strong.

88
00:08:49,370 --> 00:08:50,700
Were you happy last night?

89
00:08:53,520 --> 00:08:54,820
Yes, I was.

90
00:08:55,790 --> 00:09:01,270
So my skills haven't dropped,
after we didn't...

91
00:09:04,030 --> 00:09:04,520
Than.

92
00:09:08,880 --> 00:09:11,520
And you? Were you happy?

93
00:09:13,860 --> 00:09:15,770
I was very happy.

94
00:09:17,080 --> 00:09:18,770
Worth the long wait.

95
00:09:20,480 --> 00:09:24,490
How did no one come
into your life for years?

96
00:09:26,610 --> 00:09:29,090
Who said no one did?
There were many.

97
00:09:29,640 --> 00:09:32,640
I wasn't interested.
I waited for you.

98
00:09:33,360 --> 00:09:34,890
- Really?
- Really.

99
00:09:37,050 --> 00:09:39,150
Then what did you do?

100
00:09:41,190 --> 00:09:42,410
What do you mean?

101
00:09:43,480 --> 00:09:44,270
Well...

102
00:09:45,720 --> 00:09:46,730
Oh.

103
00:09:48,120 --> 00:09:50,150
- I had some help.
- Help?

104
00:09:52,220 --> 00:09:54,600
Like friends with benefits?

105
00:09:55,820 --> 00:09:56,740
No.

106
00:10:03,430 --> 00:10:03,930
Than.

107
00:10:06,600 --> 00:10:08,130
I didn't want anyone
to replace you.

108
00:10:09,130 --> 00:10:11,010
I just had to deal with
myself somehow.

109
00:10:20,450 --> 00:10:21,100
Kin.

110
00:10:23,720 --> 00:10:24,060
Hm?

111
00:10:25,070 --> 00:10:27,240
You're not leaving again, right?

112
00:10:28,480 --> 00:10:29,720
Can you promise me?

113
00:10:30,840 --> 00:10:31,960
I'm afraid you'll disappear again.

114
00:10:32,790 --> 00:10:34,050
I promise, Than.

115
00:10:35,560 --> 00:10:38,130
I won't walk out of your life again.

116
00:10:40,940 --> 00:10:42,670
No matter what happens,

117
00:10:44,270 --> 00:10:45,500
I'll stay right here.

118
00:10:46,650 --> 00:10:49,460
I'll stay by your side.
I won't go anywhere.

119
00:10:55,180 --> 00:10:59,950
Don't disappear, run away,
go silent, or see others.

120
00:11:01,170 --> 00:11:03,090
And don't love anyone but me.

121
00:11:04,020 --> 00:11:05,860
I allow you just one thing.

122
00:11:06,260 --> 00:11:06,810
What is it?

123
00:11:07,670 --> 00:11:09,940
I allow you to grow old before me.

124
00:11:15,710 --> 00:11:20,640
When we were kids,
I said I'd grow up fast.

125
00:11:21,140 --> 00:11:22,400
So I could ask you
to be my partner.

126
00:11:23,080 --> 00:11:26,960
Now I'm grown and I have you
back as my partner.

127
00:11:28,480 --> 00:11:31,970
If I age past you,
I wouldn't know how.

128
00:11:33,870 --> 00:11:35,270
So you can grow old first.

129
00:11:36,280 --> 00:11:39,070
Even if you're old and wrinkled,

130
00:11:39,970 --> 00:11:43,940
with crow's feet, gray hair,
or bad hearing,

131
00:11:45,340 --> 00:11:46,560
I'll still love you.

132
00:11:48,600 --> 00:11:50,440
And I'll say I love you every day.

133
00:11:51,900 --> 00:11:53,140
You promise?

134
00:11:53,890 --> 00:11:55,340
I mean it.

135
00:12:01,160 --> 00:12:02,100
I love you.

136
00:12:03,900 --> 00:12:04,720
I love you too.

137
00:12:14,480 --> 00:12:21,070
When couples wake up,
what do they do in the morning?

138
00:12:22,240 --> 00:12:25,820
They shower, wash up,
then go to work.

139
00:12:26,210 --> 00:12:28,050
So they can build a future together.

140
00:12:28,830 --> 00:12:29,690
No.

141
00:12:31,250 --> 00:12:35,130
This is what people in love do.

142
00:12:35,290 --> 00:12:37,670
Hey, Than. Than!

143
00:12:39,910 --> 00:12:43,070
Than, that's enough.
I'm going to shower.

144
00:12:43,100 --> 00:12:44,340
Just a moment.

145
00:12:44,890 --> 00:12:46,600
Hey, Than!

146
00:12:47,440 --> 00:12:50,290
- Just a moment isn't real.
- Fine, stay still then.

147
00:12:50,710 --> 00:12:53,520
This trainer will
take care of his trainee.

148
00:12:54,360 --> 00:12:55,440
Hey, Than!

149
00:12:57,150 --> 00:12:57,760
Than!

150
00:13:01,700 --> 00:13:03,500
Than! Than!

151
00:13:34,980 --> 00:13:35,900
Anything I can help with?

152
00:13:37,590 --> 00:13:38,770
Just sit back.

153
00:13:39,240 --> 00:13:41,670
Let me show my skills.

154
00:13:42,590 --> 00:13:45,280
Two sunny-side-up eggs,
not fully cooked.

155
00:13:47,920 --> 00:13:51,540
Or three,
to make up for lost energy.

156
00:14:09,560 --> 00:14:10,390
Thank you.

157
00:14:24,120 --> 00:14:27,850
Our first breakfast together
in five years.

158
00:14:29,040 --> 00:14:31,940
Getting ready to be
a full-time househusband.

159
00:14:40,830 --> 00:14:42,630
Is your condo rented?

160
00:14:43,820 --> 00:14:46,450
Yes. Did you buy or rent yours?

161
00:14:47,080 --> 00:14:47,640
Bought it.

162
00:14:48,450 --> 00:14:50,940
Paid off yet? I can help pay.

163
00:14:51,650 --> 00:14:54,240
So this can be our place.

164
00:14:54,990 --> 00:14:58,110
No need.
Aren't you the househusband?

165
00:14:58,730 --> 00:14:59,930
Pay it all yourself.

166
00:15:00,520 --> 00:15:04,260
Sure. I'll marry in
and be the family head.

167
00:15:05,420 --> 00:15:07,110
You're really over the top.

168
00:15:13,350 --> 00:15:15,350
May I break the yolk?

169
00:15:17,420 --> 00:15:21,020
Sweet-looking basketball kid,

170
00:15:21,490 --> 00:15:23,180
since when did you get so sly?

171
00:15:24,580 --> 00:15:27,190
I should handle this early.

172
00:15:28,150 --> 00:15:28,990
Before it gets worse.

173
00:15:39,120 --> 00:15:40,490
Why is my boyfriend so rough?

174
00:15:41,060 --> 00:15:42,340
Just eat. Be good.

175
00:16:30,220 --> 00:16:31,370
Are you full, Mawin?

176
00:16:31,980 --> 00:16:32,780
Yes, I am.

177
00:16:33,600 --> 00:16:35,860
Why are you mad at
Uncle Kin and Uncle Than?

178
00:16:40,540 --> 00:16:44,380
If I ask you to live
with me and study here,

179
00:16:45,100 --> 00:16:46,110
what would you say?

180
00:16:46,980 --> 00:16:49,830
Whatever you want. I love you.

181
00:16:50,350 --> 00:16:52,800
Uncle Kin says I should listen to you.

182
00:16:53,390 --> 00:16:55,800
No one loves us like parents do.

183
00:16:58,450 --> 00:17:01,940
Do you still want to have a dad?

184
00:17:04,540 --> 00:17:05,550
Uncle Kin is my dad.

185
00:17:05,950 --> 00:17:07,750
When I'm not with you,

186
00:17:08,170 --> 00:17:10,160
I let him be my dad.

187
00:17:10,660 --> 00:17:14,170
I call him Daddy Kin when we go out.

188
00:17:14,540 --> 00:17:15,790
I love him.

189
00:17:17,300 --> 00:17:21,180
I mean, do you still
want to see your real dad?

190
00:17:38,880 --> 00:17:39,690
Drop me here.

191
00:17:39,920 --> 00:17:42,430
- Catch them.
- What?

192
00:17:43,920 --> 00:17:45,340
Don't think we didn't notice.

193
00:17:46,210 --> 00:17:49,500
Two breakfast plates,
two coffee cups.

194
00:17:49,660 --> 00:17:52,580
And a status saying you're taken.

195
00:17:52,900 --> 00:17:53,810
What's going on?

196
00:17:54,340 --> 00:17:56,040
They came out of
the car together too.

197
00:17:56,290 --> 00:17:58,740
They even kissed
before getting out. I saw it.

198
00:17:58,760 --> 00:18:01,570
Don't laugh. You're a suspect too.

199
00:18:01,660 --> 00:18:03,060
Suspect of what, AJ?

200
00:18:03,290 --> 00:18:05,930
Indy and I investigated for ages.
You can't escape.

201
00:18:06,400 --> 00:18:10,130
Too said there will be
no work or meetings today

202
00:18:10,150 --> 00:18:12,020
until Beyond Perfect knows the truth.

203
00:18:12,140 --> 00:18:12,610
Exactly.

204
00:18:13,390 --> 00:18:15,630
This isn't the time to hide
the truth anymore, Than.

205
00:18:16,510 --> 00:18:19,260
It's past hiding
two people's happiness.

206
00:18:21,240 --> 00:18:23,330
It's not shameful to love someone.

207
00:18:23,520 --> 00:18:27,300
We should proudly say

208
00:18:27,330 --> 00:18:28,960
they are the one who makes us happy.

209
00:18:30,510 --> 00:18:32,020
Take those two for questioning.

210
00:18:32,480 --> 00:18:33,590
Go. Now.

211
00:18:35,540 --> 00:18:36,640
- What is this?
- What's going on?

212
00:18:38,660 --> 00:18:40,380
Let me ask directly.

213
00:18:40,730 --> 00:18:43,890
What is your relationship right now?

214
00:18:46,420 --> 00:18:49,490
- Well, before we...
- We used to be a couple.

215
00:18:51,280 --> 00:18:53,070
And now we're together again.

216
00:18:53,170 --> 00:18:56,050
Oh really, Than?

217
00:18:56,470 --> 00:18:58,740
Can you give details?

218
00:18:59,180 --> 00:19:01,940
When did you two start dating?

219
00:19:02,200 --> 00:19:03,730
Oh, AJ.

220
00:19:04,470 --> 00:19:08,310
- Great question since you're here.
- Nice.

221
00:19:09,450 --> 00:19:11,430
Than, answer him.

222
00:19:11,940 --> 00:19:16,260
Back in grade 10,
I was playing basketball.

223
00:19:16,710 --> 00:19:20,450
The ball hit him as he walked by.

224
00:19:20,750 --> 00:19:24,450
Oh wow, such a classic plot.

225
00:19:25,270 --> 00:19:27,960
What were you doing at his school?

226
00:19:28,120 --> 00:19:28,550
Well...

227
00:19:28,970 --> 00:19:30,740
I had just passed my university exam.

228
00:19:31,050 --> 00:19:33,170
So I visited my old teachers
with friends.

229
00:19:33,390 --> 00:19:36,850
So you were from the same school.

230
00:19:37,190 --> 00:19:40,210
Yes, but we didn't
know each other then.

231
00:19:40,250 --> 00:19:41,810
- Oh?
- And then?

232
00:19:42,370 --> 00:19:45,070
So you fell in love
from a ball to the head?

233
00:19:45,850 --> 00:19:47,180
You're easy, man.

234
00:19:47,700 --> 00:19:51,210
No, he fell for me first.

235
00:19:53,130 --> 00:19:54,170
Really, Than?

236
00:19:54,540 --> 00:19:58,040
Kin, don't tell me the kid flirted.

237
00:19:58,230 --> 00:20:03,080
Or you couldn't resist
that high school charm?

238
00:20:04,130 --> 00:20:05,820
Something like that.

239
00:20:09,400 --> 00:20:13,670
I admit it.
Than was my love at first sight.

240
00:20:14,990 --> 00:20:17,070
I never believed in it before

241
00:20:17,520 --> 00:20:19,010
until I met him.

242
00:20:20,690 --> 00:20:22,670
Not just because he looks good,

243
00:20:23,490 --> 00:20:26,010
but because he is truly himself.

244
00:20:26,530 --> 00:20:29,740
Honest, pure, sincere.

245
00:20:30,950 --> 00:20:34,080
Than's charm isn't just his looks.

246
00:20:35,210 --> 00:20:39,180
It's in every word and every action.

247
00:20:39,930 --> 00:20:44,440
I feel so lucky to
meet someone like him.

248
00:20:46,040 --> 00:20:49,200
Someone I don't need reasons to love.

249
00:20:49,930 --> 00:20:55,440
If it's not him,
I won't love anyone else.

250
00:20:58,080 --> 00:21:01,640
Sweeter than a sugar substitute ad.

251
00:21:01,660 --> 00:21:02,710
True. Oops.

252
00:21:02,790 --> 00:21:03,700
Hey, what's wrong?

253
00:21:04,320 --> 00:21:07,520
I don't know if I'm cringing
or just jealous.

254
00:21:09,650 --> 00:21:11,760
What do you like about him, Than?

255
00:21:11,790 --> 00:21:12,240
Well...

256
00:21:12,370 --> 00:21:16,180
Back then,
I didn't really know what love was.

257
00:21:16,770 --> 00:21:19,760
I thought he was handsome,
a huggable senior.

258
00:21:20,350 --> 00:21:24,620
Whenever he looked at me,
I wanted to be good for him.

259
00:21:25,020 --> 00:21:28,270
I felt his care and kindness.

260
00:21:28,840 --> 00:21:31,540
I wanted him to look at me
like that every day.

261
00:21:31,970 --> 00:21:33,790
Before I knew it,

262
00:21:35,820 --> 00:21:37,630
I grew up with those feelings.

263
00:21:38,770 --> 00:21:41,340
It was my first love,
still lasting today.

264
00:21:41,950 --> 00:21:44,890
Was Than your first love too?

265
00:21:50,850 --> 00:21:55,840
My gosh,
which novel did this come from?

266
00:21:56,330 --> 00:22:00,730
It's so real some people
might not understand.

267
00:22:00,980 --> 00:22:02,080
This isn't a novel.

268
00:22:02,410 --> 00:22:04,080
It's a dream many people have.

269
00:22:04,370 --> 00:22:07,080
And it came true for Than and Akin.

270
00:22:07,670 --> 00:22:11,010
So how did you get back together?

271
00:22:12,440 --> 00:22:15,790
There was a misunderstanding
in Than's first year.

272
00:22:16,520 --> 00:22:19,600
I thought he cheated
and got a girl pregnant.

273
00:22:19,750 --> 00:22:21,830
Whoa, that's intense.

274
00:22:22,520 --> 00:22:24,690
I didn't know about it at all.

275
00:22:24,860 --> 00:22:26,780
So you broke up just like that?

276
00:22:27,010 --> 00:22:29,980
You just believed it?

277
00:22:30,730 --> 00:22:34,920
See, Kin?
Even AJ knows you were way too...

278
00:22:34,950 --> 00:22:36,720
There was more before that.

279
00:22:37,250 --> 00:22:39,180
Than stayed over at a friend's dorm.

280
00:22:39,520 --> 00:22:42,310
They took a photo lying
on the same bed.

281
00:22:42,700 --> 00:22:46,490
There were condoms
and other stuff by the bed.

282
00:22:46,510 --> 00:22:48,290
But it wasn't what Kin thought.

283
00:22:48,600 --> 00:22:50,200
Those things were my friend's.

284
00:22:50,310 --> 00:22:52,500
Just normal stuff guys keep around.

285
00:22:52,520 --> 00:22:54,020
But that wasn't all.

286
00:22:54,820 --> 00:22:57,520
Than also worked at
a female friend's place.

287
00:22:57,880 --> 00:23:00,980
After that,
there was a mark on his neck.

288
00:23:01,690 --> 00:23:05,570
All the bad coincidences
hit me at once.

289
00:23:05,960 --> 00:23:07,580
An ant bit my neck.

290
00:23:07,600 --> 00:23:10,600
But it looked like
a hickey from a girl.

291
00:23:12,040 --> 00:23:13,520
It really looked convincing.

292
00:23:14,160 --> 00:23:19,210
That's why couples
need to trust each other.

293
00:23:19,460 --> 00:23:23,880
But many who trusted still got hurt.

294
00:23:23,910 --> 00:23:25,210
- Right, Fai?
- Exactly, Fai.

295
00:23:25,230 --> 00:23:26,680
It all built up.

296
00:23:26,700 --> 00:23:28,800
Then the pregnancy rumor
happened too.

297
00:23:29,010 --> 00:23:30,770
So all trust was gone.

298
00:23:31,120 --> 00:23:32,630
I thought Than really did it.

299
00:23:32,970 --> 00:23:35,810
So he left me without a word.

300
00:23:36,270 --> 00:23:39,450
Leaving me in doubt
for four or five years.

301
00:23:39,770 --> 00:23:40,760
But it's okay now.

302
00:23:41,180 --> 00:23:44,090
In the end, we met again
at Nene and Mawin's school.

303
00:23:44,280 --> 00:23:45,540
And here, in this building.

304
00:23:47,020 --> 00:23:51,000
So the call to investigate Mawin
and Akin was about this?

305
00:23:51,830 --> 00:23:53,870
I thought Mawin was Than's child.

306
00:23:54,360 --> 00:23:55,820
So I helped his mom take care of him.

307
00:23:57,360 --> 00:23:59,620
Then who is Mawin's dad?

308
00:23:59,920 --> 00:24:02,410
Sun. He's my older brother.

309
00:24:02,480 --> 00:24:04,950
- Oh.
- Your brother.

310
00:24:05,250 --> 00:24:07,520
I'll tell you the details
another time.

311
00:24:08,500 --> 00:24:10,060
I want to hear about your first kiss.

312
00:24:11,560 --> 00:24:13,890
You two broke up for years.

313
00:24:14,280 --> 00:24:16,770
- Didn't either of you...
- AJ!

314
00:24:17,310 --> 00:24:20,140
Enough. That's inappropriate.
You can't ask that.

315
00:24:20,440 --> 00:24:21,600
So how was the first kiss?

316
00:24:24,660 --> 00:24:26,640
So to sum it up,

317
00:24:26,670 --> 00:24:30,640
You two are back together
and officially dating, right?

318
00:24:33,380 --> 00:24:33,760
Yes.

319
00:24:37,870 --> 00:24:41,650
Should I ask this?
So, are you getting married?

320
00:24:46,780 --> 00:24:49,850
We still have
a few things to sort out.

321
00:24:49,870 --> 00:24:51,130
Oh, okay.

322
00:24:51,280 --> 00:24:52,480
What else is there?

323
00:24:53,250 --> 00:24:54,830
Hey, enough.

324
00:25:07,950 --> 00:25:08,960
What are you doing?

325
00:25:09,560 --> 00:25:12,210
I've seen you focused
on that notebook.

326
00:25:13,480 --> 00:25:16,390
Can you help me fill in
my family tree?

327
00:25:17,940 --> 00:25:20,320
Uncle Kin isn't my real dad.

328
00:25:21,100 --> 00:25:23,320
Should I write that I have no father?

329
00:25:23,960 --> 00:25:26,720
Or can I still write his name?

330
00:25:29,000 --> 00:25:31,240
My grandparents are in heaven.

331
00:25:31,480 --> 00:25:33,370
So I'll write they're in heaven too.

332
00:25:39,960 --> 00:25:42,430
Do I have grandparents on dad's side?

333
00:25:52,710 --> 00:25:54,560
My friends fill many boxes.

334
00:25:55,210 --> 00:25:57,440
But having just you is enough for me.

335
00:25:58,520 --> 00:26:01,520
I'll write your name really big.

336
00:26:02,120 --> 00:26:04,250
Filling the whole page
like everyone else.

337
00:26:27,940 --> 00:26:29,490
Oh, you're leaving, Than?

338
00:26:29,990 --> 00:26:31,420
Yes. Is there anything?

339
00:26:35,390 --> 00:26:36,950
It's nothing. We'll talk later.

340
00:26:37,640 --> 00:26:39,690
After you're done with love stuff.

341
00:26:40,250 --> 00:26:41,620
I need help deciding something.

342
00:26:42,200 --> 00:26:43,710
You decide. No need to wait for me.

343
00:26:44,170 --> 00:26:46,610
I'll go with your call. I'm off.

344
00:26:53,930 --> 00:26:55,860
Once you're free from romance,

345
00:26:56,470 --> 00:26:59,080
come help carry this failure, Than.

346
00:27:11,030 --> 00:27:13,430
Hello, Uncle Than, Uncle Kin.

347
00:27:54,200 --> 00:27:56,730
Oh, Nut. Closing alone again?

348
00:27:58,510 --> 00:27:59,160
Yes.

349
00:28:00,480 --> 00:28:01,690
Has it not improved at all?

350
00:28:05,740 --> 00:28:06,670
Just as you can see.

351
00:28:09,760 --> 00:28:10,710
So what do we do next?

352
00:28:20,060 --> 00:28:22,280
We may have to close this branch.

353
00:28:23,430 --> 00:28:25,900
And refocus on the first branch
that's still doing well.

354
00:28:28,800 --> 00:28:31,270
Than doesn't know
we have to close this place yet.

355
00:28:34,440 --> 00:28:35,550
He's deep in love these days.

356
00:28:39,520 --> 00:28:40,650
When we hit a dead end,

357
00:28:41,640 --> 00:28:44,630
sometimes we have to
take another path

358
00:28:45,450 --> 00:28:46,980
that lets us keep going.

359
00:28:50,480 --> 00:28:51,360
A dead end.

360
00:28:55,570 --> 00:28:56,930
I forgot about that.

361
00:28:59,880 --> 00:29:01,660
I only thought that
if I tried hard enough,

362
00:29:04,050 --> 00:29:04,930
one day,

363
00:29:07,690 --> 00:29:09,720
I'd find a way to reach him.

364
00:29:13,810 --> 00:29:16,390
Even though there were
signs all along

365
00:29:20,280 --> 00:29:21,870
that no matter how I walked,

366
00:29:26,090 --> 00:29:27,630
I'd end up at a dead end anyway.

367
00:29:33,800 --> 00:29:35,280
I think I understand you.

368
00:29:42,590 --> 00:29:44,950
The reason I opened this branch

369
00:29:47,300 --> 00:29:51,130
was so Than could fully take charge.

370
00:29:53,790 --> 00:29:56,190
I planned to support him
from a distance.

371
00:30:00,780 --> 00:30:02,990
I wanted him to have
a place to stand.

372
00:30:04,100 --> 00:30:07,160
But he stood with
someone else, not you.

373
00:30:11,800 --> 00:30:12,810
It's okay.

374
00:30:14,260 --> 00:30:16,680
Just being able to
care for him is enough.

375
00:30:18,440 --> 00:30:22,340
You wanted him to see
what you did for him, but he didn't.

376
00:30:25,360 --> 00:30:26,400
I think he did see it.

377
00:30:29,760 --> 00:30:31,970
He saw that I'm only fit
to be a big brother.

378
00:30:38,900 --> 00:30:42,780
Not everyone we love
has to love us back.

379
00:30:44,010 --> 00:30:48,660
Not everything we do with
our whole heart has to be ours.

380
00:31:02,820 --> 00:31:03,690
That's just how it is.

381
00:31:06,540 --> 00:31:08,150
So when do you have to move out?

382
00:31:11,060 --> 00:31:12,170
Probably within this month.

383
00:31:54,240 --> 00:31:56,450
Hello, Uncle.

384
00:31:56,490 --> 00:31:57,510
- Hello.
- Hello.

385
00:31:57,530 --> 00:32:00,610
Oh, I wondered who it was.
Why didn't you tell us first?

386
00:32:01,130 --> 00:32:02,650
Oh, did Mawin come too?

387
00:32:02,790 --> 00:32:03,700
Mawin.

388
00:32:05,810 --> 00:32:07,370
Someone wants to meet you.

389
00:32:09,440 --> 00:32:13,130
Oh, who's that? She's very pretty.

390
00:32:19,210 --> 00:32:21,390
This is Meya, Mawin's mother.

391
00:32:24,200 --> 00:32:25,070
Hello.

392
00:32:40,470 --> 00:32:42,090
I didn't know that...

393
00:32:43,470 --> 00:32:47,710
Sun left us before
Nene was even born.

394
00:32:50,690 --> 00:32:53,770
I know I shouldn't even
be sitting here.

395
00:32:54,710 --> 00:32:57,110
I'm not fit to be involved
with anyone.

396
00:32:57,830 --> 00:33:01,520
What happened between Sun and me
was just youthful emotions.

397
00:33:04,010 --> 00:33:07,450
I may not have started
the way everyone hoped

398
00:33:09,450 --> 00:33:11,150
but your child is my grandchild.

399
00:33:13,140 --> 00:33:16,140
Life isn't always neat and orderly.

400
00:33:17,190 --> 00:33:19,370
Sometimes it starts unintentionally.

401
00:33:19,860 --> 00:33:23,260
But in the end, it might turn into
the best gift of all.

402
00:33:24,850 --> 00:33:25,920
Like Mawin.

403
00:33:27,610 --> 00:33:30,180
Come here, come to Grandpa.
Let me give you a big hug.

404
00:33:30,520 --> 00:33:33,880
Oh my, wow.
It's like I got tackled.

405
00:33:38,770 --> 00:33:44,060
Nene, are you happy?
Mawin is your little brother now.

406
00:33:44,390 --> 00:33:46,770
What little brother?
He’s bigger than me!

407
00:33:49,330 --> 00:33:51,970
Mawin is Daddy Sun’s child too.

408
00:33:52,480 --> 00:33:55,070
Then you aren't Mawin’s dad?

409
00:34:00,580 --> 00:34:03,980
This is so confusing.
Suddenly Mawin is my brother.

410
00:34:04,500 --> 00:34:09,199
Then that means you have to share
your snacks with me all the time?

411
00:34:09,500 --> 00:34:13,040
Oolder siblings have to take care of
and sacrifice for their younger ones.

412
00:34:14,150 --> 00:34:16,190
- That sounds like forcing her.
- Totally forcing her.

413
00:34:16,560 --> 00:34:17,179
Alright.

414
00:34:17,210 --> 00:34:19,290
- Alright, Nene.
- Come to Grandma.

415
00:34:23,370 --> 00:34:24,980
My legs are completely numb.

416
00:34:26,900 --> 00:34:31,060
Children really are the best bond
for every family.

417
00:34:38,540 --> 00:34:40,280
Give your brother lots of snacks.

418
00:34:41,620 --> 00:34:43,940
Take good care of him, understand?

419
00:34:46,850 --> 00:34:47,719
Please come in.

420
00:34:54,830 --> 00:34:57,510
It feels like everything
is finally settling down.

421
00:34:59,010 --> 00:35:02,250
Even though I once thought
this day would never come.

422
00:35:13,560 --> 00:35:16,640
Bougainvillea grows well
in harsh, dry conditions.

423
00:35:16,990 --> 00:35:21,180
It withstands sun and rain,
even when the soil isn’t good.

424
00:35:21,850 --> 00:35:24,480
Yet it can still bloom beautifully.

425
00:35:25,430 --> 00:35:29,190
It’s a symbol of strength, patience,

426
00:35:29,810 --> 00:35:32,240
and beauty born from not giving up.

427
00:35:33,560 --> 00:35:35,430
It’s not easy for it to bloom.

428
00:35:36,010 --> 00:35:39,730
But once it does,
it can bloom all year round.

429
00:35:40,240 --> 00:35:42,360
It’s kind of like our love.

430
00:35:48,760 --> 00:35:53,310
We went through so many things
to finally reach today.

431
00:35:54,830 --> 00:35:58,520
Do you think we’re grown enough now?

432
00:36:03,900 --> 00:36:06,790
We really owe it to our patience.

433
00:36:08,500 --> 00:36:12,290
In the end, it turned out beautiful,
just like this bougainvillea.

434
00:36:16,870 --> 00:36:18,210
- Kin.
- Hmm?

435
00:36:19,140 --> 00:36:20,150
Stay here tonight.

436
00:36:21,190 --> 00:36:22,760
Stay? I didn’t bring anything.

437
00:36:23,470 --> 00:36:26,000
You don’t need to.
Everything’s already here.

438
00:36:26,900 --> 00:36:28,720
You can wear my clothes.

439
00:36:31,170 --> 00:36:33,870
Please… stay here tonight.

440
00:36:34,580 --> 00:36:35,820
Tomorrow’s a day off anyway.

441
00:36:38,860 --> 00:36:39,290
Please?

442
00:37:00,680 --> 00:37:02,450
- You know what this is?
- I know.

443
00:37:15,640 --> 00:37:17,500
- Betel leaves?
- Betel leaves.

444
00:37:18,920 --> 00:37:21,520
- Than, give me a fish.
- Can you eat it?

445
00:37:21,550 --> 00:37:23,090
- One whole fish, Dad?
- Yeah, one whole fish.

446
00:37:23,110 --> 00:37:24,400
It’s Mawin’s favorite.

447
00:37:25,120 --> 00:37:26,860
- Careful.
- A big bowl.

448
00:37:26,890 --> 00:37:30,160
Here you go. Eat a lot
so you’ll grow as big as Mawin.

449
00:38:02,680 --> 00:38:03,380
Have you tried it yet?

450
00:38:03,480 --> 00:38:04,850
If you scoop it and it splashes...

451
00:38:05,630 --> 00:38:07,160
Mawin, say goodbye to everyone.

452
00:38:07,600 --> 00:38:10,210
Bye, Grandpa and Grandma.

453
00:38:10,560 --> 00:38:13,090
Bye, Uncle Kin and Uncle Than.

454
00:38:13,270 --> 00:38:14,210
Bye...

455
00:38:15,210 --> 00:38:19,150
You are younger,
so you should tell me too.

456
00:38:21,110 --> 00:38:22,430
Bye, Nene.

457
00:38:23,580 --> 00:38:26,790
Good boy, little brother.
Grow up fast.

458
00:38:28,790 --> 00:38:31,520
- Wow.
- Hey, you grow up fast too.

459
00:38:31,860 --> 00:38:34,420
Look at your brother,
he’s so much bigger than you.

460
00:38:34,930 --> 00:38:36,170
Yeah, shorty.

461
00:38:38,930 --> 00:38:41,760
Pack your clothes and
stay here next week, Mawin.

462
00:38:42,400 --> 00:38:45,200
How about staying with
Grandpa and Grandma for a week?

463
00:38:45,460 --> 00:38:46,030
Okay.

464
00:38:47,730 --> 00:38:50,880
I’ll prepare a room and lots of toys.

465
00:38:51,290 --> 00:38:52,740
So we can play all day.

466
00:38:54,450 --> 00:38:56,330
Alright, let’s go.

467
00:38:56,670 --> 00:38:59,100
- Goodbye.
- Goodbye.

468
00:38:59,120 --> 00:39:00,260
Have a safe trip.

469
00:39:06,820 --> 00:39:10,090
- I have something to show you.
- What is it?

470
00:39:10,120 --> 00:39:11,950
What are you two whispering about?

471
00:39:13,010 --> 00:39:13,940
Tell me too.

472
00:39:14,950 --> 00:39:15,570
They're leaving.

473
00:39:17,340 --> 00:39:17,860
Dad.

474
00:39:18,820 --> 00:39:19,280
Yes?

475
00:39:21,670 --> 00:39:25,010
How steady must one be
to take care of someone?

476
00:39:32,530 --> 00:39:35,690
Than, don’t you have
any other clothes?

477
00:39:44,840 --> 00:39:45,530
Enough.

478
00:39:47,830 --> 00:39:49,050
Do you usually sleep
dressed like this?

479
00:39:49,980 --> 00:39:52,610
No, I got it ready for you.

480
00:39:54,180 --> 00:39:55,830
Just wear it.
You’ll take it off anyway.

481
00:39:56,080 --> 00:39:58,570
Take off what?
You bought it, you wear it.

482
00:40:00,340 --> 00:40:01,770
Then want to swap?

483
00:40:02,610 --> 00:40:03,790
I can wear yours.

484
00:40:04,280 --> 00:40:04,830
It’s fine.

485
00:40:07,750 --> 00:40:10,180
Hey, what are you doing?

486
00:40:10,910 --> 00:40:12,160
We’re swapping, right?

487
00:40:15,000 --> 00:40:17,640
If you won’t take it off,
I’ll help you.

488
00:40:19,870 --> 00:40:21,020
Your parents will wake up.

489
00:40:22,170 --> 00:40:23,850
Then don’t be loud.

490
00:40:24,480 --> 00:40:25,060
Than.

491
00:40:26,730 --> 00:40:29,960
Don’t be loud, and don’t resist.

492
00:41:00,360 --> 00:41:00,870
Than.

493
00:41:02,140 --> 00:41:02,650
Yes?

494
00:41:03,360 --> 00:41:04,880
Did you lock the front door?

495
00:41:05,740 --> 00:41:06,660
I did, Dad.

496
00:41:07,100 --> 00:41:07,610
Good.

497
00:41:15,690 --> 00:41:16,360
That’s enough.

498
00:42:31,830 --> 00:42:33,890
- Never been here, right?
- I think so.

499
00:42:34,050 --> 00:42:36,140
- Feels like an old beach.
- How do people live here?

500
00:42:36,170 --> 00:42:37,700
- Hmm.
- Where did Nene go?

501
00:42:38,590 --> 00:42:40,300
She’s probably drawing in that room.

502
00:42:41,930 --> 00:42:42,650
What about Akin?

503
00:42:43,840 --> 00:42:46,420
He’s still asleep. He looked
comfortable, so I didn’t wake him.

504
00:42:46,680 --> 00:42:47,460
Oh.

505
00:42:49,530 --> 00:42:52,900
Huh? these don’t look alike at all.

506
00:42:57,220 --> 00:42:58,230
Dad, Mom.

507
00:42:59,790 --> 00:43:02,750
You wake up to each other
every day for 30 years.

508
00:43:03,020 --> 00:43:04,250
Don’t you ever get bored?

509
00:43:05,040 --> 00:43:07,560
Oh my, why ask that?

510
00:43:08,540 --> 00:43:09,130
Yeah.

511
00:43:11,830 --> 00:43:13,090
I just want to know.

512
00:43:14,470 --> 00:43:15,830
Hmm...

513
00:43:17,500 --> 00:43:18,990
- Sometimes I do.
- What?

514
00:43:20,130 --> 00:43:24,410
But if I had no him and had to
get bored with someone else,

515
00:43:25,190 --> 00:43:26,160
I’d rather not.

516
00:43:28,450 --> 00:43:31,040
Saying I’m never bored
wouldn’t be true.

517
00:43:32,090 --> 00:43:36,610
But even when I am,
I still want to see him every day.

518
00:43:37,630 --> 00:43:39,900
This is the first time
I’ve heard this.

519
00:43:40,180 --> 00:43:40,940
Really?

520
00:43:42,590 --> 00:43:45,600
Enduring love, you see,

521
00:43:45,980 --> 00:43:48,310
isn’t about never getting bored.

522
00:43:48,960 --> 00:43:51,300
It’s about choosing to stay together.

523
00:43:52,080 --> 00:43:56,820
Even if you wake up
to a day with nothing exciting at all,

524
00:43:56,850 --> 00:44:00,000
you still want to wake up
and see the same familiar face.

525
00:44:03,260 --> 00:44:04,170
Don’t act all cute.

526
00:44:04,870 --> 00:44:07,260
I just found out you used to
get bored of me.

527
00:44:09,130 --> 00:44:10,190
That’s life.

528
00:44:11,130 --> 00:44:12,070
Let’s keep looking at this.

529
00:44:12,530 --> 00:44:14,580
I want to be like you.

530
00:44:15,250 --> 00:44:17,470
I want to wake up
and see Kin every day.

531
00:44:18,970 --> 00:44:21,650
But I’m not sure how well
I can take care of him.

532
00:44:27,250 --> 00:44:27,930
You can.

533
00:44:36,480 --> 00:44:36,860
I’m off.

534
00:44:40,830 --> 00:44:41,600
What now?

535
00:44:46,440 --> 00:44:46,940
I’m off.

536
00:44:56,260 --> 00:45:00,900
The brand aims to lead
Asia’s full-service EV industry.

537
00:45:01,420 --> 00:45:04,120
Their product is electric golf carts.

538
00:45:04,150 --> 00:45:07,290
They’re the first to
contact us directly.

539
00:45:08,300 --> 00:45:09,670
- Yes.
- Great, great.

540
00:45:14,630 --> 00:45:16,270
- Been waiting long?
- Not at all.

541
00:45:16,530 --> 00:45:17,640
You must be tired today.

542
00:45:17,750 --> 00:45:19,530
So much. Meetings all day.

543
00:45:19,700 --> 00:45:21,460
- Let me help.
- Thanks.

544
00:45:21,490 --> 00:45:22,290
The bag too.

545
00:45:22,480 --> 00:45:24,480
It’s okay. Let’s eat. I’m starving.

546
00:45:24,710 --> 00:45:25,150
Let’s go.

547
00:45:55,780 --> 00:45:57,620
- Hello, bro.
- Yeah.

548
00:46:28,020 --> 00:46:29,020
What are you reading?

549
00:46:30,220 --> 00:46:32,760
I’m reviewing client info
for tomorrow’s pitch.

550
00:46:33,980 --> 00:46:34,790
Dry my hair for me.

551
00:46:36,820 --> 00:46:37,760
Why don’t you do it yourself?

552
00:46:39,220 --> 00:46:40,270
Who usually dries it for you?

553
00:46:41,690 --> 00:46:42,980
Well, I have you now.

554
00:46:43,830 --> 00:46:45,330
I can do it myself,

555
00:46:45,800 --> 00:46:49,480
but having my boyfriend do it
feels like a life mission.

556
00:46:50,480 --> 00:46:53,190
People with partners want to
be taken care of.

557
00:46:53,680 --> 00:46:57,170
They want affection,
to stick together all the time.

558
00:47:09,170 --> 00:47:11,940
You’re not going back to your room?

559
00:47:13,610 --> 00:47:16,750
When my lease ends,
I’ll move in with you.

560
00:47:17,630 --> 00:47:20,560
Nene can stay too.
We’ll all be together.

561
00:47:21,120 --> 00:47:25,080
Morning and evening,
we can take turns picking them up.

562
00:47:25,910 --> 00:47:27,710
I’ve planned everything already.

563
00:47:48,390 --> 00:47:50,420
Let me flick this clingy head once.

564
00:47:51,750 --> 00:47:54,370
All done. Go get changed
and get some sleep.

565
00:47:57,940 --> 00:47:59,100
Who said I’m sleeping?

566
00:48:02,190 --> 00:48:04,200
Hurry, put your clothes on.

567
00:48:05,250 --> 00:48:06,840
Why? I’ll just take them off again.

568
00:48:08,970 --> 00:48:10,020
Not tonight.

569
00:48:10,870 --> 00:48:11,680
Why not?

570
00:48:12,870 --> 00:48:13,730
Recovery.

571
00:48:14,400 --> 00:48:15,230
Recovery from what?

572
00:48:16,100 --> 00:48:17,580
Well, Than...

573
00:48:18,920 --> 00:48:21,950
Okay then, tonight,

574
00:48:22,910 --> 00:48:28,480
I’ll play a clueless high schooler
who knows nothing in bed.

575
00:48:29,000 --> 00:48:32,380
Should a college senior teach him?

576
00:48:35,980 --> 00:48:37,930
Hey, don’t you ever get tired?

577
00:48:38,630 --> 00:48:39,640
No, I don't.

578
00:48:40,350 --> 00:48:40,850
Please?

579
00:48:42,480 --> 00:48:43,950
I’ll be as gentle as possible.

580
00:48:45,980 --> 00:48:47,090
Can I trust that?

581
00:48:58,290 --> 00:48:59,560
Is this gentle enough?

582
00:49:17,150 --> 00:49:21,490
my heart is yours, the only one.

583
00:49:21,600 --> 00:49:24,470
It’s always been, it’ll always stay,

584
00:49:24,670 --> 00:49:29,880
I’d never turn my love away.

585
00:49:31,340 --> 00:49:34,510
And meeting you again today,

586
00:49:35,740 --> 00:49:39,110
I realize, though years have flown,

587
00:49:39,300 --> 00:49:45,820
My heart’s still yours,
you’re still my own.

588
00:49:47,440 --> 00:49:51,060
It’s been so long since last we met,

589
00:49:51,100 --> 00:49:54,920
yet you’re the same I can’t forget.

590
00:49:56,440 --> 00:50:03,250
Just like the days we used to share,
those memories linger everywhere.

591
00:50:03,610 --> 00:50:07,400
Tell me, love, are you doing fine,

592
00:50:08,130 --> 00:50:11,490
When I no longer walk beside your line?

593
00:50:12,290 --> 00:50:15,580
I hope you miss me after all,

594
00:50:16,790 --> 00:50:23,100
the way my heart
still hears your call.

595
00:50:26,030 --> 00:50:29,410
I hope you miss me after all,

596
00:50:33,590 --> 00:50:45,420
the way my heart
still hears your call.

597
00:51:13,710 --> 00:51:16,580
Wake up, sweetheart.
You’ll be late for work.

598
00:51:17,490 --> 00:51:19,180
A bit longer?

599
00:51:20,950 --> 00:51:21,790
What longer?

600
00:51:22,690 --> 00:51:26,330
Than, can I sleep a little more?

601
00:51:32,440 --> 00:51:34,420
Can you even work like this?

602
00:51:39,210 --> 00:51:42,480
I said recovery,
but you wouldn’t listen.

603
00:51:45,480 --> 00:51:46,380
Did you like it though?

604
00:51:52,140 --> 00:51:52,790
Come on.

605
00:51:54,150 --> 00:51:55,330
Get up now, sweetheart.

606
00:51:56,050 --> 00:51:58,310
I’ll get dressed and make breakfast.

607
00:52:07,480 --> 00:52:09,310
Come on, get up.

608
00:52:10,450 --> 00:52:12,000
If not, I’ll go for round two.

609
00:52:13,040 --> 00:52:14,670
Go on. Can you handle it?

610
00:52:19,730 --> 00:52:21,290
Are you challenging the system?

611
00:52:22,340 --> 00:52:25,350
I just want to see if you can.

612
00:52:28,880 --> 00:52:30,210
Just kidding. Go shower.

613
00:53:11,490 --> 00:53:13,110
I thought I came early.

614
00:53:13,870 --> 00:53:15,760
Why are you always here first?

615
00:53:17,830 --> 00:53:21,880
Try being more serious.
Maybe you’ll come earlier.

616
00:53:24,130 --> 00:53:26,440
Why so serious this morning?

617
00:53:29,310 --> 00:53:32,560
We have to move out by month’s end.

618
00:53:37,240 --> 00:53:40,680
Some equipment will be
sold secondhand.

619
00:53:42,090 --> 00:53:45,920
The newer machines will go
to the first branch.

620
00:53:47,010 --> 00:53:48,700
And replace the old ones there.

621
00:53:52,800 --> 00:53:55,670
Why so fast? This month?

622
00:53:57,140 --> 00:54:00,090
It’s not fast.
I’ve stalled for months.

623
00:54:01,670 --> 00:54:05,180
Sorry. I really can’t hold on anymore.

624
00:54:07,780 --> 00:54:10,000
I think it’s still possible.

625
00:54:10,640 --> 00:54:14,440
Small losses could be covered
by the other branch.

626
00:54:15,690 --> 00:54:17,010
We’ve covered it for months.

627
00:54:18,970 --> 00:54:20,110
But it won’t survive.

628
00:54:22,020 --> 00:54:26,510
The location’s good,
but locals’ lifestyles differ.

629
00:54:27,180 --> 00:54:28,410
Not what we expected.

630
00:54:40,340 --> 00:54:42,070
Shouldn’t we fight a bit more?

631
00:54:43,350 --> 00:54:45,210
We already have regulars.

632
00:54:45,860 --> 00:54:49,300
If we tweak the plan,
it could still work.

633
00:54:51,420 --> 00:54:53,040
I’m afraid it’ll be wasted effort.

634
00:54:54,080 --> 00:54:56,040
And you don’t have time
for this place.

635
00:54:58,000 --> 00:55:01,460
Better put our full effort into
the first branch.

636
00:55:02,660 --> 00:55:05,920
Then find a new spot
if we want to try again.

637
00:55:07,870 --> 00:55:11,650
Are you saying I didn’t try
hard enough here?

638
00:55:12,980 --> 00:55:13,980
And with Akin?

639
00:55:16,230 --> 00:55:18,130
How much do you give him?

640
00:55:19,260 --> 00:55:22,500
Think of him from
waking till sleeping.

641
00:55:23,330 --> 00:55:25,670
Even dream of him.

642
00:55:27,330 --> 00:55:30,480
Do things for him
without being asked.

643
00:55:32,200 --> 00:55:34,570
And here, this fitness center...

644
00:55:36,350 --> 00:55:38,680
Have you ever loved it like that?

645
00:55:46,250 --> 00:55:48,100
I’m not blaming you.

646
00:55:50,330 --> 00:55:55,020
People have different
focuses at each life stage.

647
00:55:56,350 --> 00:56:00,330
You may want stability
in love and your heart.

648
00:56:01,160 --> 00:56:02,250
That’s not strange.

649
00:56:03,300 --> 00:56:07,190
It’s normal not to
focus here as much.

650
00:56:09,750 --> 00:56:12,280
So what are you focused on now?

651
00:56:17,060 --> 00:56:19,980
Part of it is life stability.

652
00:56:22,170 --> 00:56:24,250
And the other thing
I’ve never stopped focusing on

653
00:56:25,770 --> 00:56:26,490
is you.

654
00:56:27,720 --> 00:56:30,000
I kept trying to
make this gym succeed

655
00:56:31,290 --> 00:56:33,150
because I wanted you
to be proud of himself,

656
00:56:34,320 --> 00:56:35,670
to feel secure in life.

657
00:56:36,730 --> 00:56:38,220
And honestly, without shame...

658
00:56:40,490 --> 00:56:44,510
deep down, I also wanted you
to see that I’m the one

659
00:56:46,120 --> 00:56:48,790
who helped make
your life better bit by bit.

660
00:56:49,110 --> 00:56:51,910
I’ve always seen it.
It’s not that I didn’t.

661
00:56:53,210 --> 00:56:55,050
– But I...
– Yeah, yeah.

662
00:56:55,990 --> 00:56:58,520
Hey, forget it.

663
00:57:00,740 --> 00:57:02,970
No one gets everything
they want in life.

664
00:57:05,200 --> 00:57:06,520
There has to be disappointment.

665
00:57:08,970 --> 00:57:10,130
Business is the same.

666
00:57:14,750 --> 00:57:19,310
But you’ve never made me feel
like I lost anything

667
00:57:22,250 --> 00:57:22,920
from loving you

668
00:57:26,860 --> 00:57:28,470
even if it’s only as your brother.

669
00:57:32,540 --> 00:57:35,940
Just being able to love is
already worth it.

670
00:57:44,640 --> 00:57:48,350
I’m sorry that I can only
give you this much.

671
00:57:50,360 --> 00:57:54,010
And thank you for always
taking care of me

672
00:57:55,320 --> 00:57:56,240
in every way.

673
00:57:57,880 --> 00:58:00,510
And I’m still willing to
help you going forward.

674
00:58:08,050 --> 00:58:11,970
Don’t overthink it.
We still have another branch.

675
00:58:13,560 --> 00:58:16,800
And we still have to give it
our all to make it better.

676
00:58:19,140 --> 00:58:22,060
Come on, let’s push forward
with the first branch.

677
00:58:22,580 --> 00:58:26,250
And wait for the chance
to open a new one later.

678
00:58:28,600 --> 00:58:29,170
Alright.

679
00:58:29,740 --> 00:58:31,940
Our product is a luxury vehicle

680
00:58:32,210 --> 00:58:34,270
but we want to present it
in a contrasting way

681
00:58:34,400 --> 00:58:36,950
by switching the background
to a more minimalist style.

682
00:58:37,900 --> 00:58:40,240
These are all ideas proposed
by Beyond Perfect.

683
00:58:41,050 --> 00:58:42,220
– Sounds good.
– Yeah.

684
00:58:42,770 --> 00:58:44,060
– It’ll work, bro.
– Yeah.

685
00:58:47,740 --> 00:58:50,910
I’m not sure minimalism
is still trending.

686
00:58:51,760 --> 00:58:54,340
I want something more vibrant,

687
00:58:54,880 --> 00:58:57,680
bold colors, big fonts,
instantly memorable.

688
00:58:58,090 --> 00:59:00,900
And the model, I want someone sexy.

689
00:59:01,400 --> 00:59:04,190
A strong figure,
something eye-catching.

690
00:59:04,440 --> 00:59:07,370
As for clothes,
load them with brand names.

691
00:59:07,940 --> 00:59:10,350
Show that our car is luxurious.

692
00:59:11,080 --> 00:59:11,670
Okay.

693
00:59:11,980 --> 00:59:16,130
And one more thing,
I checked the budget handled before.

694
00:59:16,420 --> 00:59:17,790
I think it was way over the top.

695
00:59:18,340 --> 00:59:21,930
I’m going to cut the budget in half.

696
00:59:31,080 --> 00:59:34,370
The previous person you mentioned,
you mean Mr. Don?

697
00:59:35,680 --> 00:59:39,850
Yes, my experience may not match his

698
00:59:40,250 --> 00:59:43,830
but I’ve handled quite
a few major projects too.

699
00:59:44,550 --> 00:59:48,700
Beyond Perfect may need to adjust
our working direction together.

700
00:59:52,830 --> 00:59:56,610
If you have time, look at
the projects Mr. Don handled.

701
00:59:57,920 --> 00:59:58,930
Then you’ll understand

702
00:59:59,460 --> 01:00:02,600
why people in the industry
regret his departure so much.

703
01:00:05,530 --> 01:00:06,540
That impressive?

704
01:00:07,410 --> 01:00:11,620
Alright then, if I have time,

705
01:00:12,370 --> 01:00:14,670
I’ll study his past work.

706
01:00:16,560 --> 01:00:20,170
But for this project,
please revise it for me

707
01:00:20,760 --> 01:00:23,070
because I’m the one still here

708
01:00:24,400 --> 01:00:26,130
and managing this project.

709
01:00:26,980 --> 01:00:27,290
Yes.

710
01:00:27,810 --> 01:00:30,430
Mind, set a meeting within this week.

711
01:00:31,060 --> 01:00:35,630
And list other interesting
production houses for me.

712
01:00:39,670 --> 01:00:41,170
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

713
01:00:42,090 --> 01:00:43,890
- See you, Mind.
- Bye.

714
01:00:49,720 --> 01:00:50,370
Ugh.

715
01:00:51,450 --> 01:00:53,980
Seeing this client
makes me miss Mr. Don.

716
01:00:54,000 --> 01:00:54,490
Yeah.

717
01:00:54,510 --> 01:00:57,920
That guy was perfect.
Super talented.

718
01:00:58,540 --> 01:01:00,630
He could silence
the whole meeting room

719
01:01:00,830 --> 01:01:02,210
because everyone wanted to listen.

720
01:01:03,300 --> 01:01:04,690
This guy can too

721
01:01:05,760 --> 01:01:06,690
but from awkwardness.

722
01:01:08,560 --> 01:01:09,150
True.

723
01:01:09,840 --> 01:01:12,850
Ugh, he rejected
everything we proposed.

724
01:01:14,510 --> 01:01:15,130
Yes, Mom.

725
01:01:16,510 --> 01:01:18,380
- One moment, please.
- Sure, Akin.

726
01:01:20,670 --> 01:01:23,550
- Did you write that down?
- I did.

727
01:01:24,400 --> 01:01:25,230
Everything needs fixing.

728
01:01:29,410 --> 01:01:31,750
What did the doctor say, Mom?

729
01:01:36,510 --> 01:01:39,470
If it takes that long,
what about work here?

730
01:01:41,570 --> 01:01:44,120
Okay, I’ll arrange things quickly.

731
01:01:44,250 --> 01:01:45,780
I’ll go as soon as I can.

732
01:01:47,060 --> 01:01:49,520
Please tell Dad
I’ll come see him soon.

733
01:01:50,690 --> 01:01:51,700
I love you both.

734
01:02:17,830 --> 01:02:18,540
- Than.
- Kin.

735
01:02:20,260 --> 01:02:21,210
You go first.

736
01:02:22,130 --> 01:02:23,090
No, you first.

737
01:02:23,620 --> 01:02:25,280
You go. What is it?

738
01:02:27,830 --> 01:02:31,520
The second gym branch
might have to close.

739
01:02:32,440 --> 01:02:34,310
Probably by the end of this month.

740
01:02:35,800 --> 01:02:38,060
I thought it was still manageable.

741
01:02:39,720 --> 01:02:41,130
I thought so too.

742
01:02:41,610 --> 01:02:45,580
But after seeing the numbers,
it won’t work.

743
01:02:46,650 --> 01:02:49,200
We’ll focus on branch one first.

744
01:02:49,640 --> 01:02:51,350
Then think about expanding again.

745
01:02:52,480 --> 01:02:54,490
Is there anything
you want my help with?

746
01:02:55,650 --> 01:02:56,840
No need to.

747
01:02:57,360 --> 01:03:00,650
Don’t worry.
The first branch is doing fine.

748
01:03:01,210 --> 01:03:02,610
I can still cover
your condo payments.

749
01:03:04,090 --> 01:03:07,380
It’s okay, Than.
I was just joking about that.

750
01:03:12,030 --> 01:03:16,130
I’m afraid you won’t trust me
to take care of you.

751
01:03:18,400 --> 01:03:20,800
I want stability in life
as soon as possible.

752
01:03:23,080 --> 01:03:26,710
I never wanted you
to take care of me.

753
01:03:28,250 --> 01:03:29,930
I just want you in my life.

754
01:03:41,260 --> 01:03:44,920
But if there’s something
that makes you wait,

755
01:03:47,660 --> 01:03:49,130
can you wait for me again?

756
01:04:08,940 --> 01:04:10,530
Go do what you need to do.

757
01:04:11,420 --> 01:04:14,700
One day, it’ll be our time.

758
01:04:15,340 --> 01:04:17,490
Kids, say hello to Uncle Kin.

759
01:04:17,530 --> 01:04:19,060
- Hello.
- Hello.

760
01:04:19,670 --> 01:04:20,920
Bye-bye.

761
01:04:21,390 --> 01:04:22,780
Hey.

762
01:04:22,810 --> 01:04:24,990
Look who I brought today.

763
01:04:27,290 --> 01:04:28,200
Kin.

764
01:04:28,700 --> 01:04:29,820
Oh, they're here.

765
01:04:30,090 --> 01:04:32,610
I still love Than
just the same as always.

766
01:04:35,540 --> 01:04:36,560
I love you.
